THIS STATION WAS ACTIVATED IN AUGUST, 1980 FOR THE COLLECTION      
OF BASELINE INTENSIVE SURVEY DATA.  KEAUHOU BAY IS A SMALL BAY WITH     
HEAVY BOATING TRAFFIC UTILIZING THE KEAUHOU BOAT HARBOR LOCATED IN      
THE BAY.  THERE ARE NUMEROUS HOMES AND A HOTEL SITUATED ON THE          
SOUTHERN SHORE OF THE BAY.  THE SAMPLING STATION IS IN THE CENTER       
OF THE BOAT CHANNEL IN APPROXIMATELY 30 FEET OF WATER.
